The paper discusses the development of an annotation tool for dialogue data, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The tool also integrates machine learning models as annotation recommenders, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The tool is designed to improve the speed and quality of dialogue data annotation, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The tool also has a dedicated interface to resolve inter-annotator disagreements, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the tool is open source and publicly available, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
